headline: PAYC Q1 Earnings Call: Automation and International Expansion Shape 2025 Outlook
summary: Online payroll and human resource software provider Paycom (NYSE:PAYC) reported Q1 CY2025 results topping the market’s revenue expectations, with sales up 6.1% year on year to $530.5 million. The company expects the full year’s revenue to be around $2.03 billion, close to analysts’ estimates. Its non-GAAP profit of $2.80 per share was 9.4% above analysts’ consensus estimates.

headline: Paycom returns to favor
summary: Paycom, the star of the SaaS sector—for once a legitimate one—has made a successful comeback on the stockmarket.
